 19 ### Phosh 0.38.0 Release
 20
 21 The well-known and much-loved GNOME-based mobile desktop environment, Phosh, just saw its 0.38.0 release.
 22
 23 => https://phosh.mobi/ Phosh homepage
 24
 25 As usual, Phosh itself, as well as the Phoc compositor, and Squeekboard, Phosh's onscreen keyboard, all saw some quality-of-life improvements. Here's a quick breakdown of the new features and fixes:
 26
 27 ~ Phosh updates
 28
 29 - Lock screen launcher entries can display count and progress status.
 30 - Improved handling on devices with rounded corners.
 31 - Fixed some issues with background scaling noticed in Phosh 0.37.0.
 32 - The session startup for gnome-session 46.
 33 - data: URIs can now be handled in the media player.
 34 - There were new i18n updates from a variety of community translators.
 35
 36 => https://phosh.mobi/releases/rel-0.38.0/#phosh-0380-1 Phosh changes
 37
 38 ~ Phoc updates
 39
 40 - Allow views to be placed always-on-top.
 41 - Clients can now check for hardware keyboards.
 42 - Phoc was updated to wlroots 0.17.2.
 43 - There were fixes to fractional scaling.
 44 - layer-shell version was bumped to 3.
 45 - Move-to-corner is now allowed via keybinds.
 46 - Subsurfaces and Popups are now GObjects.
 47 - There were also a variety of internal fixes and cleanups, with improvements made to the build system with regards to how files are validated.
 48
 49 => https://phosh.mobi/releases/rel-0.38.0/#phoc-0380 Phoc changes
 50
 51 ~ Squeekboard updates
 52
 53 - "PgUp" and "PgDn" (PageUp and PageDown, respectively), have new arrowed labels.
 54 - Every available keyboard layout now has a wide shape, with 25 new wide shapes available.
 55 - Terminal layout key names for French and Spanish are now translated.
 56 - The development date was brought up to Debian Testing (trixie).
 57 - Various other fixes and layout files cleanup.
 58
 59 => https://phosh.mobi/releases/rel-0.38.0/#squeekboard-1380 Squeekboard changes
 60
 61 If you run a mobile Linux distro with Phosh as your mobile environment, these updates should make their way to you fairly quickly depending on which distribution you use.
