124 ### Linux Phone App Highlight
125
126 As usual, we have a few free software mobile apps to spotlight. If this is your first roundup, we share a few of our favorite apps on Linux phones and AOSP devices each time, in the hopes that more people learn about them.
127
128 * Buran: Buran is an Android app great for AOSP devices. It is a dedicated mobile web browser for the Gemini protocol, and can be customised and tweaked in various ways. I like finding and reading new Gemini capsules, and I find myself opening this app frequently for my Gemini browsing.
129 * Amethyst: Another application for AOSP, this is a client app for the Nostr protocol. Nostr is a newer decentralised social networking protocol, and it has been a lot of fun to use and build on over the last couple of years. I might do a bigger writeup into Nostr someday, but it is quite simple - your identity is managed by a private and public key, much like a crypto wallet. If you want to check it out, Amethyst is a great client app for the protocol.
130 * Tuba: Tuba is a GTK application for accessing Fediverse instances (things in the ActivityPub family, such as Mastodon and Pleroma). The app is well-designed, and it allows you to create posts, interact with others' posts, and other things you would expect to do with your favorite Fediverse client apps. Being GTK based, it also blends well in GNOME-based environments.
131
